Since even at the vertex (minima), the function gives negative value the funciton is always negative.

quest_title: Two coils have mutual inductance 0.005 H. The current changes in the first coil according to equation \(i=i_0\,\sin\omega t\) where \(i_0=10\,A\) and \(\omega=100\pi \, \text{rad/sec}\). The maximum value of e.m.f. in the second coil is
explanation_txt:
\(M=0.005 \mathrm{H} ; \quad i_{0}=10 \mathrm{A} \)

\(i=i_{0} \sin \omega t ; \omega=100 \pi \)

\(E=M \cfrac{d i}{d t}=M \cfrac{d\left(i_{0} \sin \omega t\right)}{d t}=M i_{0} \omega \cdot \cos \omega t \)

\(\text { For maximum emf, } \cos \omega t=1 \)

\(E=0.005 \times 10 \times 100 \times \pi \)

\(E=5 \pi \,\mathrm{volt} \)
